description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Medical Staffing Office, the successful applicant will be a pro-active team player with good organisational and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To work with the Medical Staffing team to support the department with managing the winter pressures for agency staffing requests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have a good general standard of education and have relevant experience of working in a hospital environment. They should be able to demonstrate good IT, office and admin skills and be fully conversant in MS Office. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vacancy is for 25 hours per week. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cheryl Chaffe Tel: 0151 678 5111 ext 2988 or via email cheryl.chaffe@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
